<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-544-101  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 544 101.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Feb 26 1990 n356 p12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Curing viruses through education, legislation. (computer viruses)(CRN Forum) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jerger, Douglas C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>There are two issues more dangerous than computer viruses:ignorance about their effects and a legal system that cannot deterpotential perpetrators.andP;  Ignorance about computer viruses can meanlost work, lost revenue and lost reputation.andP;  Lack of adequatecomputer crime laws hampers prosecution and punishment ofperpetrators.andP;  Software vendors and trade associations need towork together to eliminate ignorance and help draft legislation toprovide effective tools to punish perpetrators.andP;  This two-prongedapproach means external communication to educate computer usersabout viruses as well as intra-industry communications to handlesuch issues as propagation via shrink-wrapped software and theresulting liability and loss of reputation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesLegal IssuesEducationData SecurityPlanningLegislationComputer Crimes.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>